Preact signals are far superior to other state management patterns for react, but don't use a ContextProvider as shown is this article, pass the signals as props instead.e.g:  function MyComponent({ disabled }: { disabled: Signal<boolean> }) {
    // ...
  }

React is crazy because someone thought this was too complicated for developers:    event.listenTo(render);
    event.emit();

And that we should do this instead:    property.listenTo(render);
    property.set([property.get()[0]]);
